06:28.341 --> 06:30.386
Charles would be so upset if we bailed.

06:30.425 --> 06:31.681
But what if Charles never knew?

06:31.706 --> 06:33.153
If we can figure out
where he's going to be

06:33.177 --> 06:34.621
at the end of the night,
we don't have to do

06:34.645 --> 06:36.451
- any of his dumb puzzles.
- Right.

06:36.476 --> 06:37.821
Instead, we can spend the next six hours

06:37.845 --> 06:39.111
eating and drinking and

06:39.216 --> 06:40.880
talking about how we lost our V cards.

06:40.911 --> 06:42.779
And then we show up
at the final location

06:42.804 --> 06:44.236
and pretend we did the stupid hunt.

06:44.261 --> 06:45.883
- Yeah-yeah...
- Interesting.

06:46.155 --> 06:48.062
All right, I'm not saying
I'm on board with this

06:48.087 --> 06:50.093
'cause it's a little bit cruel,
but hypothetically,

06:50.127 --> 06:51.693
- if we were to cheat...
- Got it.

06:51.728 --> 06:53.028
I hacked his email.

06:53.063 --> 06:54.963
His password's really easy to guess.

06:54.998 --> 06:56.105
[TOGETHER] "Dianne Wiest."

06:56.130 --> 06:57.291
And look here.

06:57.382 --> 06:59.402
There's a receipt for
a party boat rental

06:59.427 --> 07:01.105
and also a cake delivery

07:01.138 --> 07:02.871
to a dock down in Bergen Beach.

07:02.906 --> 07:04.639
That's got to be where this night ends.

07:04.675 --> 07:05.720
All right, fine.

07:05.818 --> 07:07.986
We will stop and get
one tiny, little snack

07:08.011 --> 07:09.744
just to recharge our brains and bods,

07:09.780 --> 07:11.662
but under no circumstances will we

07:11.687 --> 07:14.187
