09:33.590 --> 09:35.824
- Yeah, Constantine!
- Thank you.

09:35.859 --> 09:36.925
Namaste.

09:36.960 --> 09:38.193
Look, in my defense,

09:38.228 --> 09:39.794
he didn't used to have that man bun.

09:39.830 --> 09:41.204
It was just a ponytail.

09:41.229 --> 09:42.998
I'm just gonna write
some of my thoughts down

09:43.033 --> 09:45.000
just to let them out,
so I don't explode.

09:45.035 --> 09:48.870
Okay, look, no matter how lame
that dude's man purse is,

09:48.905 --> 09:51.006
Amy Santiago still had
a one-night stand.

09:51.041 --> 09:52.741
- To Amy!
- ALL: Amy!

09:52.776 --> 09:54.342
- Yeah.
- [GLASSES CLINK]

09:54.378 --> 09:58.260
Actually, it technically
wasn't just one night.

09:58.285 --> 10:00.022
- Explain.
- Well, he caught me

10:00.047 --> 10:01.613
trying to sneak out the next morning,

10:02.028 --> 10:03.895
and then he started crying,

10:03.920 --> 10:05.253
so I hugged him, and

10:05.289 --> 10:07.222
while we were hugging, um,

10:07.257 --> 10:10.258
his mom FaceTimed,
and he introduced me as his girlfriend.

10:10.294 --> 10:11.826
Okay, so then right after the call,

10:11.862 --> 10:13.196
you broke up with him, ended it.

10:13.221 --> 10:14.929
- Uhh...
- How long were you with

10:14.965 --> 10:16.439
crying wedding-band man bun?

10:16.464 --> 10:18.366
Not that long. I doubt
he even remembers me.

10:18.402 --> 10:20.117
Oh, my God. Amy Santiago.

10:20.142 --> 10:21.303
Ladies and gentlemen,

10:21.338 --> 10:23.501
the love of my life is here.

10:24.298 --> 10:25.874
Three months. We dated
for three months.

10:25.909 --> 10:28.209
- [SIGHS] All right.
- This is the boat.

10:28.245 --> 10:30.556
Now, Charles has to think
we're totally sober

10:30.581 --> 10:31.846
and we solved his puzzle.

10:31.882 --> 10:33.588
- So we good?
- Yep, I'm drunk as hell!

10:33.613 --> 10:35.588
- That's not what I asked.
- Don't worry about me.

10:35.613 --> 10:37.176
I've seen you do enough of
these harebrained schemes

10:37.200 --> 10:38.253
to know how to play along.

10:38.288 --> 10:39.788
If Charles asks what's wrong,

10:39.823 --> 10:42.426
I'll just put on a quaint smile and say,

10:43.528 --> 10:44.726
[HIGH-PITCHED] "Nothing."

10:44.761 --> 10:46.472
Amazing. That is actually perfect.

10:46.497 --> 10:48.258
All right, now let's hold on
to each other for balance

10:48.282 --> 10:50.198
like three totally sober grown men.

10:50.233 --> 10:51.324
Come here.

10:52.369 --> 10:53.825
And here we go.

10:54.866 --> 10:56.747
Oh, yeah, we're nailing this.

10:57.661 --> 11:00.141
Hello? Charles?

11:00.166 --> 11:01.654
[LIONEL RICHIE'S "ALL NIGHT LONG" PLAYS]

11:01.678 --> 11:03.745
Surprise! Welcome to the party, pal!

11:03.780 --> 11:06.147
Wow! This is amazing!

11:06.183 --> 11:08.214
Yeah! Now we get to the best part.

11:08.239 --> 11:09.519
Steaks and shots!

11:09.544 --> 11:12.363
Ohh, more meat and alcohol.

11:12.388 --> 11:13.722
"More?" What does that mean?

11:13.757 --> 11:16.291
[TOGETHER] Uhh...

11:16.326 --> 11:18.093
[HIGH-PITCHED] Nothing?

11:21.261 --> 11:25.162
<i>[PENSIVE MUSIC]</i>

11:26.098 --> 11:27.950
- Isn't this great?
- Uh-huh.

11:28.013 --> 11:30.355
So there is one question
about the scavenger hunt

11:30.521 --> 11:31.758
you have to answer.

11:31.891 --> 11:33.806
Was he everything you thought he'd be?

11:34.328 --> 11:35.338
Yes.

11:35.374 --> 11:38.047
He was everything I thought he'd be.

11:38.072 --> 11:41.384
Never before has a person so
perfectly met my expectations.

11:41.455 --> 11:42.588
I know!

11:42.619 --> 11:44.213
Isn't Reginald VelJohnson the best?

11:44.238 --> 11:46.293
Reginald VelJohnson? From "Die Hard"?

11:46.332 --> 11:48.336
Sergeant Powell was a
part of my bachelor party?

11:49.344 --> 11:51.529
Is what I said upon meeting him.

11:51.554 --> 11:53.179
I'm just still emotional about it.

11:53.204 --> 11:55.227
I can't believe you pulled that off!

11:55.252 --> 11:56.326
[CHUCKLING] Yeah, I did.

11:56.361 --> 11:57.861
I have one more surprise for you.

11:58.472 --> 12:00.903
If I could have your eyes, ears,

12:00.981 --> 12:02.365
and emotional cores...

12:02.401 --> 12:04.402
[VITAMIN C'S "GRADUATION" PLAYS]

12:04.427 --> 12:06.280
I'd like to take you all on a journey.

12:06.305 --> 12:07.949
Wow, you got a lot of
photos of my birth.

12:07.974 --> 12:09.879
Your mom didn't have any pics,
so I had to call the hospital.

12:09.903 --> 12:11.097
- Ah.
- Jake Peralta.

12:11.214 --> 12:13.303
My partner. My best friend.

12:13.328 --> 12:15.203
My brother. My idol.

12:15.332 --> 12:18.300
The one man who has never let me down.

12:18.477 --> 12:20.196
Oh, that's very kind.

12:20.297 --> 12:22.625
Tonight had to be the biggest,

12:22.719 --> 12:24.828
most special bachelor party ever.

12:24.953 --> 12:27.891
It had to be extraordinary because you,

12:28.133 --> 12:30.711
my friend, are no ordinary man.

12:30.782 --> 12:35.632
In fact, you are 24 karat gold.

12:36.092 --> 12:37.400
♪ ♪

12:38.131 --> 12:40.197
<i>♪ So if we get the big
jobs and we make... ♪</i>

12:40.241 --> 12:43.765
24 karat gold!

12:43.796 --> 12:44.997
- Is that a phrase I say?
- No.

12:45.022 --> 12:46.191
Like the coins from the hunt!

12:46.216 --> 12:47.871
- Yes, of course.
- From those.

12:47.896 --> 12:51.153
Now, Terry, please
present your gold coin.

12:51.178 --> 12:52.926
My gold coin? The hell?

12:52.951 --> 12:55.080
From the last stop,
the one with Reginald VelJohnson.

12:55.105 --> 12:57.004
Yes, right, I already told you
that I was there and I met him.

12:57.028 --> 12:59.333
Stop bringing it up.
Terry, give the man his coin!

12:59.358 --> 13:01.604
- The hell are you talking about, Jake?
- The coin. Give him the coin.

13:01.628 --> 13:03.085
- What coin? I don't have a...
- You give him a coin.

13:03.109 --> 13:04.622
- Give him his gold coin.
- What's going on, guys?

13:04.646 --> 13:06.233
All right, here's the deal.

13:06.327 --> 13:09.415
Terry's coin fell out of his pocket,
and we lost it.

13:09.440 --> 13:11.149
We just didn't have the
heart to tell you.

13:11.174 --> 13:13.274
Oh, no. That cost $800.

13:13.299 --> 13:14.750
All right, Terry will pay me back later.

13:14.774 --> 13:17.333
- What?
- Captain, your coin, please.

13:18.076 --> 13:19.741
<i>♪ And as our lives change ♪</i>

13:19.766 --> 13:21.389
- I ate mine.
- You ate your coin?

13:21.414 --> 13:22.701
Yes, I thought it was chocolate.

13:22.976 --> 13:25.718
But you hate chocolate.
It has "too much taste."

13:25.835 --> 13:27.233
[SIGHS] Oh, man.

13:28.566 --> 13:30.460
You guys didn't do the
scavenger hunt, did you?

13:30.980 --> 13:33.104
And you call yourselves The Batch Boys?

13:33.151 --> 13:35.050
Actually, we call ourselves
The Steak Studs.

13:35.126 --> 13:36.456
Raymond!

13:36.481 --> 13:37.680
Why?

13:37.705 --> 13:40.194
- [GRUNGE MUSIC PLAYING]
- I know why you're here, Turtle Bug.

13:40.219 --> 13:41.685
I feel like the fact that you just

13:41.710 --> 13:43.210
called me that means you don't.

13:43.259 --> 13:45.939
Uh, quick question:
If I make fun of Constantine

13:45.971 --> 13:47.737
does that count as making fun of you?

13:47.762 --> 13:49.194
- Yes.
- Okay.

13:49.219 --> 13:51.219
- Can I make fun of you?
- I'd rather you didn't.

13:51.244 --> 13:53.246
Well, I have to remove
myself from this situation.

13:53.299 --> 13:56.000
Look, I want to talk to you
about a gig you have coming up.

13:56.247 --> 13:57.846
- Jake Peralta booked it.
- Yeah.

13:57.871 --> 13:58.875
- Your wedding.
- What?

13:58.900 --> 14:00.644
If you knew that, then
why did you take it?

14:00.668 --> 14:01.699
I wrote you a love song.

14:01.724 --> 14:03.534
I'm gonna sing it,
and I'm gonna win you back.

14:03.559 --> 14:05.423
Then we're gonna be on "The Today Show."

14:05.457 --> 14:07.491
- I love Hoda.
- Yeah, no.

14:07.580 --> 14:08.946
No, we will not.

14:09.084 --> 14:10.683
This is what's gonna happen, okay?

14:10.708 --> 14:11.951
You're gonna call Jake,

14:12.065 --> 14:13.641
tell him something came up,

14:13.666 --> 14:14.965
and you have to cancel the gig.

14:14.990 --> 14:16.987
Not happening.
I'm gonna get on that stage.

14:17.012 --> 14:18.811
And I'm gonna play "Amy Come Back."

14:18.836 --> 14:20.869
- Fine.
- I'm gonna tell Jake everything.

14:20.927 --> 14:23.408
I'm cancelling your band. Boom.

14:23.433 --> 14:26.034
- Okay!
- That'll just cost you $15,000.

14:26.234 --> 14:27.239
Excuse me?

14:27.264 --> 14:28.702
Well, when I heard it was your wedding,

14:28.726 --> 14:30.560
I knew your fiancé would cancel

14:30.585 --> 14:32.719
when he found out about us, so...

14:32.843 --> 14:35.143
I put in a huge kill fee.

14:35.210 --> 14:37.603
- [GASPS]
- Yeah, he never even noticed.

14:38.034 --> 14:40.701
He didn't read the terms and conditions.

14:40.925 --> 14:43.085
Look, Charles, I'm
sorry that we cheated,

14:43.110 --> 14:44.499
but your puzzle was too hard.

14:44.524 --> 14:46.351
Oh, don't give me that excuse.

14:46.430 --> 14:47.602
I worked hard on this night!

14:47.627 --> 14:48.960
And it all led up to this moment

14:48.985 --> 14:51.595
where everyone gives you
$3,200 in gold coins!

14:51.620 --> 14:53.945
Again, is the gold coin thing
based on something I said?

14:54.003 --> 14:56.137
You're 24 karat gold!

14:56.162 --> 14:57.545
- Yeah, right, okay.
- You guys are the worst.

14:57.569 --> 14:59.794
You're right, and we
shouldn't have lied to you.

14:59.901 --> 15:01.734
But all of this, the puzzle,

15:01.770 --> 15:03.408
it's what you wanted, not me.

15:03.689 --> 15:05.454
I just wanted to hang
out with my friends.

15:05.479 --> 15:07.546
Well, don't let me stop you.

15:07.632 --> 15:10.062
You can hang out with your friends
all you want, because I'm leaving.

15:10.086 --> 15:11.139
Charles!

15:11.164 --> 15:12.964
<i>[FIREWORKS POPPING]</i>

15:13.077 --> 15:14.276
Come on, slideshow.

15:18.446 --> 15:20.452
Boyle isn't picking up
and I called Genevieve.

15:20.513 --> 15:22.073
- She doesn't know where he is.
- Wait.

15:22.206 --> 15:24.728
I bet Charles is looking for the
coins he hid all over the city.

15:24.753 --> 15:25.784
They were so expensive.

15:25.809 --> 15:27.927
Also, why does he keep
saying I'm 24 karat gold?

15:27.953 --> 15:29.212
- No idea.
- Makes zero sense.

15:29.237 --> 15:30.619
We'll have to figure it out later.

15:30.644 --> 15:32.066
In the meantime, we
gotta find those coins.

15:32.090 --> 15:33.527
Yes, but how do we figure
out where they are?

15:33.551 --> 15:34.710
All we have to do is solve

15:34.735 --> 15:36.905
the entire six-hour
scavenger hunt immediately.

15:36.962 --> 15:39.005
Raymond, toss me that sextant.

15:39.030 --> 15:40.711
Guys, we can do this!

15:40.736 --> 15:42.351
- [SEXTANT THUDS]
- We cannot do this.

15:42.376 --> 15:43.594
We're way too drunk. [SIGHS]

15:43.619 --> 15:45.907
But there has to be someone that
knows where those coins are, right?

15:45.931 --> 15:47.003
Charles.

15:47.072 --> 15:48.459
- Charles would know.
- Brilliant!

15:48.484 --> 15:50.552
We just have to find Charles,
but where might he be?

15:50.576 --> 15:51.989
He's probably digging up the gold coins.

15:52.013 --> 15:53.944
But who would know where
the gold coins are?

15:53.969 --> 15:55.777
Charles! Charles knows where they are.

15:55.802 --> 15:57.776
But where is he...
No, wait we're stuck in a loop.

15:57.801 --> 15:59.127
We're super drunk and we're in a loop.

15:59.151 --> 16:01.384
We need to find someone
who isn't Charles

16:01.420 --> 16:02.686
who knows where the coins are.

16:02.754 --> 16:04.454
<i>[KNOCKING]</i>

16:04.523 --> 16:05.989
[GASPS]

16:06.124 --> 16:07.592
Oh, my God, oh, my God,
oh, my God, oh, my God.

16:07.616 --> 16:09.140
- It's Reginald VelJohnson.
- What's going on?

16:09.164 --> 16:10.390
- Who are you?
- I'm Jake Peralta.

16:10.414 --> 16:11.859
You were part of my
bachelor party tonight.

16:11.883 --> 16:13.349
Oh, you're the jerk who didn't show.

16:13.498 --> 16:15.622
He knows who I am.

16:17.235 --> 16:19.002
[SOFT SQUEAL]

16:19.254 --> 16:21.682
Okay, so I need to come up with 15 grand

16:21.715 --> 16:24.875
or my father/daughter dance is
going to be performed by that.

16:24.943 --> 16:26.895
Wrong. You're forgetting
the most obvious option.

16:26.942 --> 16:28.056
Steal the contract and destroy it.

16:28.080 --> 16:30.380
Destroy a legal document?
I can't do that.

16:30.449 --> 16:32.520
You were right, I'm a boring square

16:32.567 --> 16:36.453
who's never actually had a crazy,
stranger bone session.

16:36.521 --> 16:38.759
Gina, your looks are just
as hurtful as your words.

16:38.784 --> 16:40.790
I'm sorry. I can only control so much.

16:40.859 --> 16:42.692
- I shouldn't have come back.
- Okay. Look.

16:42.728 --> 16:44.426
You don't have to steal it. We will.

16:44.451 --> 16:45.562
- Right?
- Hell yeah.

16:45.587 --> 16:46.827
You guys don't have to do this.

16:46.852 --> 16:48.299
We told you. We're your bridesmaids.

16:48.323 --> 16:49.337
We have your back. Okay.

16:49.362 --> 16:51.015
I think if we distract
him, I can sneak in

16:51.040 --> 16:52.931
and take the contract
out of his man purse.

16:52.956 --> 16:54.264
Won't he know what's going on?

16:54.296 --> 16:55.505
He saw all of us with Amy.

16:55.790 --> 16:56.973
Not all of us.

16:57.579 --> 16:58.679
Sick set.

16:58.704 --> 17:00.025
You were really jamming up there.

17:00.080 --> 17:02.064
- Oh... [SOFT LAUGH]
- I'm Lucious Lyon.

17:02.096 --> 17:04.381
Record executive at...
Executive Records.

17:04.483 --> 17:06.707
Lucious Lyon. I've heard that name.

17:06.785 --> 17:08.729
Anyway, we're always
looking for new talent.

17:08.753 --> 17:10.553
"We" being me and my partner.

17:10.589 --> 17:12.789
That's Cookie. Let me introduce you.

17:12.824 --> 17:15.025
<i>[PLAYFUL UPBEAT MUSIC]</i>

17:15.127 --> 17:17.060
[IMITATES BIRD SCREECHING]

17:17.162 --> 17:18.494
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:18.563 --> 17:20.606
Where is it? Where is it?

17:20.631 --> 17:22.280
Why are there so many scarves in here?

17:22.305 --> 17:23.503
You looking for this?

17:23.702 --> 17:25.635
[IMITATES BIRD SCREECHING, TRILLING]

17:25.704 --> 17:27.161
I see him, Gina. Thank you.

17:27.185 --> 17:28.371
[IMITATES BIRD SCREECH]

17:28.396 --> 17:29.786
Look, Sergeant Powell,

17:29.811 --> 17:31.271
oh, I'm sorry, is it
okay if I call you by

17:31.295 --> 17:32.519
your character name from "Die Hard"?

17:32.543 --> 17:33.590
- No.
- Okay.

17:33.615 --> 17:35.793
Look, Reginald, do you know
why Charles hired you?

17:35.903 --> 17:38.024
Because I love "Die Hard"
more than any other movie,

17:38.049 --> 17:39.854
- and I loved you in it.
- For the record,

17:39.879 --> 17:41.412
I loved you from "Family Matters."

17:41.651 --> 17:43.933
Carl Winslow made me
want to become a cop.

17:43.972 --> 17:45.253
Come on, Terry, you already have

17:45.278 --> 17:46.660
like six other reasons you became a cop.

17:46.684 --> 17:48.535
This is not your moment.
And for the record,

17:48.560 --> 17:49.845
that's the first time I've ever heard

17:49.869 --> 17:50.888
him even mention "Family Matters."

17:50.912 --> 17:52.678
- Look, it's late.
- Please leave.

17:52.720 --> 17:55.087
Come on. Look... My best
friend is out there.

17:55.246 --> 17:57.077
And you're the only one
who knows where he is.

17:57.102 --> 17:58.901
So, as much as I hate to do this,

17:58.951 --> 18:00.914
you're gonna tell us where
those coins are hidden,

18:00.939 --> 18:03.084
- or you're gonna regret it.
- What are you gonna do to me?

18:03.108 --> 18:05.208
Stay here all night, making this sound:

18:05.277 --> 18:10.046
[HIGH-PITCHED SCREECH]

18:10.115 --> 18:11.378
Fine, fine.

18:11.683 --> 18:13.109
- I'll tell you where he is.
- Yes.

18:13.134 --> 18:14.217
Thank you so much.

18:14.242 --> 18:15.542
Also, we're gonna need
you to take us there,

18:15.566 --> 18:17.132
'cause we're all too drunk to drive.

18:17.322 --> 18:19.922
You thought you could
distract me with a record deal?

18:19.991 --> 18:22.588
Please, I'm already represented,

18:22.613 --> 18:23.726
by my mom.

18:23.751 --> 18:25.683
- God, you're a turd.
- Well, this turd

18:25.929 --> 18:28.113
is your best friend's future husband.

18:28.333 --> 18:29.892
- Doink!
- Hey, wait, no!

18:29.983 --> 18:31.850
- Give that back to me!
- I'm wild!

18:32.037 --> 18:35.138
- Keep going! Keep going!
- [SCREAMING]

18:35.206 --> 18:37.640
- He's gaining on you.
- Not for long.

18:37.709 --> 18:39.575
Free shots for everyone!

18:39.644 --> 18:40.677
[CHEERS]

18:40.745 --> 18:42.178
Turtle Bug!

18:42.280 --> 18:43.946
[CHEERS]

18:44.015 --> 18:45.281
Whoo!

18:45.350 --> 18:46.783
Buh-bye, Connie!

18:46.851 --> 18:49.052
Tell your mother I said
I never loved you,

18:49.087 --> 18:51.649
and that your whole family
is a bunch of friggin...

18:51.674 --> 18:53.140
- [HEAVY THUD]
- [CROWD GASPS]

18:53.291 --> 18:56.059
- Oh.
- [SCATTERED GASPS]

18:56.161 --> 18:58.127
Whoo, I broke a rule!

18:58.196 --> 19:00.229
[CHEERS]

19:00.254 --> 19:02.082
Never have I ever slept with a guy,

19:02.114 --> 19:04.089
broken his heart,
hired him to play at my wedding,

19:04.135 --> 19:05.835
stolen a legally binding
contract from him,

19:05.870 --> 19:07.737
jumped on a bar and
dumped booze on everyone,

19:07.762 --> 19:09.910
fallen off the bar,
probably given myself a concussion...

19:09.934 --> 19:11.185
[SLAMS TABLE] and a permanent scar.

19:11.209 --> 19:13.276
- I have ever!
- [CHEERS]

19:13.345 --> 19:15.812
Well, it is officially after midnight,

19:15.880 --> 19:18.047
so I can now say whatever I want.

19:18.116 --> 19:19.215
- [INHALES SHARPLY]
- Uh-oh.

19:19.284 --> 19:20.983
Tonight was awesome,

19:21.052 --> 19:22.952
and I loved hanging out with your dorks.

19:23.021 --> 19:24.987
- What?
- Aww, yeah.

19:25.016 --> 19:26.067
- [GLASSES CLINK]
- [SOFT LAUGHTER]

19:26.091 --> 19:27.248
You know, the word "dork"

19:27.273 --> 19:29.905
is actually a Celtic
word meaning "lungfish."

19:29.961 --> 19:31.791
Kylie, I'm trying so hard.

19:32.012 --> 19:33.622
This is where he told
me to wait for you.

19:33.647 --> 19:35.014
Oh, my God. This is the corner where

19:35.038 --> 19:37.598
John McClane met Zeus
Carver in "Die Hard 3."

19:37.840 --> 19:39.476
Oh, Charles. Yes, you're here.

19:39.501 --> 19:41.070
What's going on? How did you find me?

19:41.095 --> 19:42.105
Did you solve the puzzle?

19:42.207 --> 19:43.339
No, they didn't.

19:43.408 --> 19:44.532
They cheated again.

19:44.657 --> 19:45.687
Reginald.

19:45.712 --> 19:47.968
Hey man, look.
I just wanted to say I'm sorry.

19:48.063 --> 19:50.234
No, I'm the one who should apologize.

19:50.281 --> 19:51.487
I overdid it tonight.

19:51.512 --> 19:53.565
I wanted everything to
be perfect, because

19:53.787 --> 19:56.121
it's our last big night
before you get married.

19:56.187 --> 19:57.868
I guess I was a little worried

19:58.123 --> 19:59.593
things were gonna change between us.

19:59.618 --> 20:02.125
Oh, Charles. Come on.

20:02.386 --> 20:04.152
Of course, things are gonna change.

20:04.206 --> 20:05.705
I'm getting married.

20:05.730 --> 20:07.864
I mean, didn't you make
me less of a priority

20:07.899 --> 20:09.718
when you and Genevieve got together?

20:12.437 --> 20:13.813
- Yes.
- See?

20:14.133 --> 20:16.239
I mean, no matter what,
we'll always be best friends.

20:16.307 --> 20:17.974
- [SIGHS]
- Hey, you know why

20:17.999 --> 20:19.397
I didn't like your scavenger hunt?

20:19.422 --> 20:20.804
'Cause it was stupid
and overcomplicated.

20:20.828 --> 20:22.027
And way too long.

20:22.052 --> 20:23.685
- There was no food.
- Or drinks.

20:23.710 --> 20:24.867
This is not a group conversation, guys.

20:24.891 --> 20:27.178
Well, you could have stood
a little farther away from us then.

20:27.202 --> 20:28.251
Point taken.

20:28.353 --> 20:29.745
I didn't like it because

20:29.794 --> 20:31.760
you got kidnapped right
at the beginning.

20:31.878 --> 20:33.433
You were gone for six hours.

20:33.458 --> 20:35.714
I wanted to spend my
bachelor party with you.

20:36.988 --> 20:38.019
[SOFT LAUGH]

20:38.044 --> 20:39.444
I can't believe you pissed off

20:39.469 --> 20:41.367
